The paper deals with the use of deep neural networks for indoor navigation, specifically for obstacle detection and mapping. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) as well as computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of uncertainty estimation in deep models, which is relevant to the field of control systems (cs.SY).
